Davide Gaetano (sysdfg@gsusgi1.Gsu.EDU) wrote:

:   One question, how hard is it, to take one algorithm, and when you are
:   done, pad the it so that it had the biases of some other algorithm ?

:   And how effective would this be at blocking, slowing cryptoanalysis 
:   of the message ??

That's "security through obscurity," worth at most a few measly bits
of entropy.

One should always assume that an attacker knows the system being used,
just not the key. 

